(1)在通往锻工房的大道上，走着一位魁梧健壮的老工人，浓黑的眉毛下，闪动着一对机警的眼睛。这位程海师傅，退休快半年了，可三天两头总要到长年累月战斗过的锻工房去走一走，看一看，干一干。
// 左：工业学大庆 右：大干快上 //
(1) A tall and sturdy veteran worker walked down the road leading to the forging shop. Beneath his thick, black eyebrows, sharp, alert eyes gleamed. This was master worker Cheng Hai, who had retired almost half a year ago. However, every few days he would still go to the forging shop where he had worked for years to walk around, take a look, even do some work.
// Left: Learn from Daqing in Industry Right: Go all out and go fast //

(2)今天，他进厂后听说徒弟小汤被批准加入共青团，心里有说不出的高兴，想着小汤的进步，不由得加快了步伐，准备找他说上几句。
// 热烈祝贺汤大刚同志光荣加入中国共青团！(公告栏上的通知) 鼓足干劲，力争上游(公告栏上的标语) //
(2) Today, after entering the factory, he heard that apprentice, Xiao Tang, had been admitted into the Communist Youth League, [and he] was too happy to say anything. Thinking about Xiao Tang’s progress, [he] couldn’t help but quicken his pace, ready to talk with [Xiao Tang] for a bit.
// Warm congratulations to Comrade Tang Dagang on his honorable admission to the Communist Youth League of China! (Notice on the bulletin board) Work hard, strive for the upper reaches. (Slogan on the bulletin board) //

（24）白求恩到达军区司令部，第一句话就问：“伤员在哪里？”同志们劝他休息几天，他说：“我是来工作的，不是来休息的。”第二天一早天蒙蒙亮，他就动身，翻过两道山，赶到六十里外松岩口后方医院。
// 【画面中墙上的文字】打倒日本帝国主义！ 民族革命战斗万岁！ 中国共产党万岁！ //
(24) Upon arriving at the military region headquarters, Bethune’s first question was: “Where are the wounded?” Comrades advised him to rest for a few days, but he said: “I came to work, not to rest.” At dawn the next day, he set off, crossing two mountains to reach the Songyankou field Hospital sixty li away.
// [Inscription on the wall, inside the panel] Fight Japanese imperialism! Long live the people’s revolutionary struggle! Long live the Chinese Communist Party! //

(3)锻工房门口，小汤正在对一个年轻的女同志比划着说：“我们从来不叫师傅的真名，大伙都叫‘他锤子师傅’。有一次，我把一节料扔到废品堆，他知道了，用‘锤子’把我头脑中大手大脚的思想彻底锤掉才罢休……”
// 学理论，促大干！(横幅上的标语) //
(3) At the entrance of the forging shop, Xiao Tang was gesticulating to a young female comrade, saying, “We never call the master by his real name. Everyone calls him ‘Hammer Master.’ Once, I threw a piece of material into the scrap pile, and when he found out, he wouldn’t stop until he used the ‘hammer’ to thoroughly rid me of my wasteful habits…”
// Study theory, promote going all out! (Slogan on the banner) //

(5)程海打量着面前的女同志：她二十四、五岁，身穿蓝色的工作服，剪着齐耳的短发，清秀的脸上两只眼睛分外明亮。程海只觉得好面熟呀，可是在哪里见过她，却一时记不起了。
// 抓革命，促生产 (墙上的标语) //
(5) Cheng Hai looked over the young woman comrade in front of him: she was 24 or 25 years old, wearing a blue work uniform and short, ear-length hair. [She had] two exceptionally bright eyes in her delicate face. Her face seemed vaguely familiar to Cheng Hai, but he couldn’t remember where he had seen her before.
// Focus on revolution, promote production. (Slogan on the wall) //

（63）一次前线战斗，战地医疗队运载医药器材的大车被山石挡住了去路。白求恩正焦急时，忽见一个老乡赶着一头小毛驴很快从身边走过。他望着毛驴背上的“粪驮子”高兴地叫起来：“嗯，有办法了！……
(63) During a frontline battle, the medical convoy’s supply cart got blocked by fallen boulders. Just as Bethune grew frantic, a local farmer came trotting past with a little donkey. His eyes lit up at the sight of the “dung carrier ” on its back of the donkey. “Ah! Here’s our solution!” he exclaimed.
// The “dung carrier ”: A distinctive donkey harness used in North China villages—willow-woven saddle baskets traditionally for transporting animal dung or manure, though adaptable for other loads. //

（79）白求恩对群众无比热爱，经常背着药箱到各村巡视。有次，人群中冲出一位老大娘，急迫地说：“白大夫，我家媳妇得了重病，日夜叫喊疼痛，人已瘦得皮包骨，请了好些医生都没法治……”
// 【画面中墙上的文字】打倒日本帝国主义！ 民族革命战斗万岁！ 中国共产党万岁！ //
(79) Bethune had an immense love for the people and often patrolled different villages with his medical kit on his back. On one occasion, an elderly woman rushed out from the crowd and said urgently, “Doctor Bai, my daughter-in-law is gravely ill. She has been crying out in pain day and night, is wasted to skin and bones. We’ve consulted many doctors, but none of them could cure her&hellip;”
// [Inscription on the wall, inside the panel] Fight Japanese imperialism! Long live the people’s revolutionary struggle! Long live the Chinese Communist Party! //

(8)一队朝气勃勃的同学抬着焦炭、废铁走来，程海见了称赞说：“看他们多认真啊！”卓红告诉程海：“有一个同学没有来，他开始逃学了。”
// 安全生产(程海衣服上的标签) //
(8) A group of spirited pupils walked towards [them] carrying coke and scrap iron. Cheng Hai saw them and praised, “Look how dedicated they are!” Zhuo Hong told Cheng Hai, “One pupil didn’t come. He’s started skipping school.”
// Work safety (label on Cheng Hai’s jacket) //

(9)“跟他家长谈谈嘛！”程海认真地说，“我们小时候想读书还读不上呢。”卓红急切地说：“是呀，这些同学都还小，如果我们放松警惕，资产阶级就会腐蚀他们……”
// 千万不要忘记阶级斗争！(墙上的标语) //
(9) “Talk to his parents!” Cheng Hai said earnestly, “Back in my childhood, we wanted to study but didn’t have the chance.” Zhuo Hong said in an imperative tone, “Exactly, these pupils are still young. If we relax our vigilance, the bourgeois class will corrupt them&hellip;”
// Never forget class struggle! (Slogan on the wall) //

(16)程海缓慢地说：“是啊，我想讲讲我们那孩子……”一句话勾起了老伴辛酸的往事，她掏出手帕擦了擦眼角。程海想起刚才看到的情形，坚定地说：“现在的孩子生在新社会，泡在甜水里，不晓得过去是什么世道啊。”
// 光荣退休 (墙上的奖状) //
(16) Cheng Hai responded slowly: “Yes, I want to talk about our child&hellip;” His words evoke poignant memories for his wife, [and] she pulled out a handkerchief to wipe the corners of her eyes. Recalling what he had seen just now, Cheng Hai spoke with determination, “Today, children are born into this new society. They grow up in comfort and ease. But they have no idea what the world was like in the past.”
// Honorable Retirement (Certificate on the wall) //

(25)为了弄清男孩的住址，同他家长谈谈，中午放学的时候，程海站在百货公司一旁等着。不一会，那个男孩走来了。
// 日夜商店 (商店的牌子) //
(25) To find out the boy’s address and talk to his parents, Cheng Hai waited by the department store when school let out at noon. After a short while, the boy walked by.
// Day and Night Store (Store Sign) //

(27)那人继续说：“我这个人最讲义气，要抽烟，尽管说，嘴上一叼，多神气……”站在一旁的程海听了，只觉得血直往脸上涌，他恨不能一把抓住这个坏家伙。但他忍住了：这是一场争夺下一代的战斗啊！
// 为人民服务 (橱窗里的横幅) 安全生产(程海衣服上的标签) //
(27) The man continued, “I really value loyalty. If you want to smoke, just let me know. With a cigarette in [your] mouth, [you will look] so cool.” Cheng Hai, standing nearby, felt blood rushing to his face. He wished he could have grabbed this scoundrel at once. But he held back, [telling himself], this is a fight for the next generation!
// Serve the People (banner in the window)
Work safety (label on Cheng Hai’s jacket) //

(50)正在这时，小贝、小汤和另一个青工拥了进来。“看！”小贝举着一把锈迹斑斑的活络扳手，说：“戴旧便帽的人叫我今晚到一家厂后面的临时库房去偷马达，偷到后给我十元……”
// 上 (青工外套上) //
(50) Just then, Xiaobei, Xiao Tang, and another young worker swarmed in. Xiaobei held up a rust-stained adjustable wrench and said, “Look! The man with the shabby cap told me to go to a temporary warehouse behind a factory to steal a motor tonight. He said he’d give me ten yuan if I succeeded.”
// up (label on the young worker’s jacket) //

(58)批斗大会在学校的操场上召开。那天晚上，由于天黑，程海没有看清戴旧便帽人的脸，现在他认出了那人就是解放前的国民党特务兼工头，名叫刁青云。顿时，一幕幕往事浮现在眼前……
// 加强无产阶级专政 (牌子上的标语) //
(58) The struggle session was held on the school’s sports ground. That night, due to the darkness, Cheng Hai hadn’t seen the face of the man with the shabby cap clearly. Now, he recognized him as Diao Qingyun, a former Guomindang spy and a foreman from before the liberation. Suddenly, scenes from the past flashed before his eyes&hellip;
// Consolidate the dictatorship of the proletariat. (Slogan on sign) //

(82)老赵还没有回答，“哗”的一声门被推开了。在外听了一阵的卓红，手里拿着那张发黄了的“当票”，含着喜悦的泪花，飞快地冲进来，对着程海喊了一声“爸爸！”
// 红旗(桌上的书的封面)人民日报 (后面的报纸上) //
(82) Before Secretary Zhao could respond, the door suddenly “whooshed” open. Zhuo Hong, who had been listening outside for a while, rushed, holding the yellowed pawn ticket in her hand, her eyes filled with tears of joy. She cried out to Cheng Hai: “Dad!”
// Red Flag (cover of the book on the table) People’s Daily (on the newspaper at the back) //

(83)程海一惊，接过“当票”，明白了。他张开双臂把卓红紧紧搂在怀里……。老赵在一旁感动地笑着，不知说什么才好。
// 共产党万岁！毛主席万岁!(墙上的标语) //
(83) Cheng Hai was shocked. As he took the pawn ticket, he understood everything. He stretched out both arms and held Zhuo Hong tightly in his embrace&hellip; Next to them, Secretary Zhao smiled, deeply moved, and didn’t know what to say.
// Long live the Communist Party! Long Live Chairman Mao! (Slogans on the wall) //
